            <h1>Tagged Questions</h1>


<div id="tabs">
        <a href="/tags/pairs-trading/info" title="information about this tag">info</a>
        <a class="youarehere" href="/questions/tagged/pairs-trading?sort=newest&pageSize=15" title="The most recently asked questions">newest</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/pairs-trading?sort=frequent&pageSize=15" title="Questions with the most links">frequent</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/pairs-trading?sort=votes&pageSize=15" title="Questions with the most votes">votes</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/pairs-trading?sort=active&pageSize=15" title="Questions that have recent activity">active</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/pairs-trading?sort=unanswered&pageSize=15" title="Questions that have no upvoted answers">unanswered</a>
</div>
        </div>
        <div class="question">


            <div class="welovestackoverflow" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <div style="float: left;">
                        <p>
Pairs trading is a market-neutral trading strategy enabling traders to profit from virtually any market conditions: uptrend, downtrend, or sideways movement. This strategy is categorized as a statistical arbitrage and convergence trading strategy.                         </p>
                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            <a title="tag wiki" href="/tags/pairs-trading/info">learn more&hellip;</a>
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="top answerers and askers in this tag" href="/tags/pairs-trading/topusers">top users</a> 
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="common, alternate spellings or phrasings for this tag" href="/tags/pairs-trading/synonyms">synonyms (1)</a>
                                                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

